WEBVTT

00:03:00.423 --> 00:03:04.103
"My sister, who is pregnant,
is bleeding. What should I do?

00:03:04.127 --> 00:03:05.301
Who should I turn to?"

00:03:05.325 --> 00:03:07.455
"Where are the doctors,
where are the nurses?

00:03:07.479 --> 00:03:10.240
If I could find one, are they trustworthy?

00:03:10.264 --> 00:03:12.997
How will I pay them?
In what currency will I pay them?"

00:03:13.021 --> 00:03:15.815
"If I need medications,
where will I find them?

00:03:16.844 --> 00:03:19.739
If I take those medications,
are they actually counterfeits?"

00:03:19.763 --> 00:03:21.262
And on and on.

00:03:22.945 --> 00:03:25.317
So for life in these settings,

00:03:25.341 --> 00:03:29.821
the dominant theme,
the dominant feature of life,

00:03:29.845 --> 00:03:33.788
is the incredible vulnerability
that people have to manage